{
  "texts": [
    "What parameters can one manipulate, if any?",
    "LLMs are based on neural networks, which were first conceptualized in 1943 (Macukow, 2016), that generate output through transfer learning.",
    "Transfer learning is the method of taking a model trained on one task to use for a second, related task.",
    "This is done as a way to optimize and enable rapid progress when modeling the second task.",
    "Let's imagine that a model's first task was to identify a horse and black and white stripes, and the second task was to identify a zebra."
  ]
}